  "text": "Production of expression constructs. A construct for the expression of the bC1 gene of TYLCCNB, under the control of a duplicated CaMV 35S promoter has been described previously [CITATION_1] . The C4 genes of TYLCCNV and Y194 were amplified by PCR using specific primer pairs Y10AC4F/Y10AC4R and Y194AC4F/ Y194AC4R, respectively, cloned in pGEM-T and sequenced. Each of the C4 fragments was then cloned into the binary vector pBin438 at BamHI and SalI sites to yield pBin438-TYLCCNVC4 and pBin438-Y194C4, respectively. The pBin438 vector lacking an insert and pBin438 constructs were introduced into A. tumefaciens EHA105 by triparental mating.",
